# .placeholder-ignore — paths exempted from validate-placeholders.sh
# (one glob per line; '#' starts a comment)
#
# The placeholder validator flags unfilled `[[TOKEN]]` and literal `YYYY-MM-DD`
# date-format tokens. Tula uses `YYYY-MM-DD` extensively as *documentation of
# the memory-file naming convention* (e.g. `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`),
# not as unfilled placeholders. These are legitimate and must not trip the gate.
#
# Governance/template-derived artifacts (docs/adr, docs/product, docs/testing,
# docs/operating-principles.md, etc.) are deliberately NOT exempted — that is
# exactly where real unfilled [[TOKEN]]s from harness templates should be caught.

# Skill sources and references document the YYYY-MM-DD memory-path convention.
skills/**

# Agent-workspace deploy templates reference the dated memory-file convention.
docs/agent/**

# Operator scripts mention the dated backup/commit naming convention.
scripts/**

# Project README documents the workspace memory layout (YYYY-MM-DD.md).
README.md
